------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
classic capture
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
works for all databases
data changes are captured from redologs/archive logs
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
integrated capture mode
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
from 11.2 version onwards, the extract process communicated with the database logminning server and recives information in the form of logical change record called LCR
this is only for extract process, the extract process gets the data from log mining server
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Implementing Classic and Integrated Captures
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
GGSCI> ADD EXTRACT ETTND001, TRANLOG, BEGIN NOW

GGSCI> ADD EXTTRAIL /app/ggs/tiger/dirdat/t1, EXTRACT ETTND001

GGSCI> ADD EXTRACT PFTXD001, EXTTRAILSOURCE /app/ggs/tiger/dirdat/t1

GGSCI> EDIT PARAMS ETTND001

EXTRACT ETTND001
USERID tiger, PASSWORD tiger123_
EXTTRAIL /app/ggs/tiger/dirdat/t1
TABLE TIGER.ORDER_DTL;


GGSCI> EDIT PARAMS PFTND001

EXTRACT PFTND001
USERID tiger, PASSWORD tiger123_
RMTHOST node2.ravin-pc.com, MGRPORT 7809
RMTTRAIL /app/ggs/fox/dirdat/f1
PASSTHRU
TABLE TIGER.ORDER_DTL;

if you are using Oracle Wallet then below commands
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
GGSCI> EDIT PARAMS ETTND001

EXTRACT ETTND001
USERIDALIAS tiger
LOGALLSUPCOLS
ENCRYPTTRAIL AES192
EXTTRAIL /app/ggs/tiger/dirdat/t1
TABLE TIGER.ORDER_DTL;

GGSCI> EDIT PARAMS PFTND001

EXTRACT PFTND001
USERIDALIAS tiger
RMTHOST node2.ravin-pc.com, MGRPORT 7809 ENCRYPT AES192, KEYNAME mykey1
RMTTRAIL /app/ggs/fox/dirdat/f1
PASSTHRU
TABLE TIGER.ORDER_DTL;
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

ggsci> start *



